Date: Wed 18 Sep 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Direction de la sante publique de Montreal-Centre, West Nile
virus surveillance results, Fri 13 Sep 2002 [edited]
<http://206.167.52.1/santpub/bulletinvno.nsf/49dd266bd183416e852566e2005c98b6/fbeb0709415031d985256b99004f758b?OpenDocument>

Quebec: Surveillance Results, as of Fri 13 Sep 2002
---------------------------------------------------
The following is a summary of the results of West Nile virus
surveillance in the province of Quebec as of Fri 13 Sep 2002.
Birds:
In total 91; Montreal-Centre 30, Laurentides 8, Outaouais 4, Mauricie
et Centre-du-Quebec 2, Monteregie 35, Laval 6, Estrie 4,
Chaudierie-Apalaches 2.
Mosquito pools:
In total 7; Laurentides 3, Monteregie 3, Montreal-Centre 1.
Humans:
In total 3 probable cases awaiting final confirmation;
Montreal-Centre 2, Laurentides 1.
******
[3]
Date: Wed 18 Sep 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ontario Department of Health and Long Term Care, news
release, Tue 17 Sep 2002 [edited]
<http://www.newswire.ca/government/ontario/english/releases/September2002/17/c1867.html>

Ontario: Surveillance results as of Tue 17 Sep 2002
---------------------------------------------------
Birds:
A total of 235 bird from 34 regions of the provinces have been
confirmed West Nile virus-positive.
Mosquitoes:
A total of 71 mosquito pools from 11 regions of the province have
tested West Nile virus-positive.
Humans:
As of Tue 17 Sep 2002 there have been 3 confirmed cases (1 fatal) and
14 probable cases of West Nile virus infection in the province:
Haldimand-Norfolk 1 (probable); Halton 3 (probable),1 (confirmed);
Middlesex-London 1 (probable); Peel 4 (probable), 2 (confirmed);
Toronto 4 (probable); and Windsor 1 (probable). One of the
individuals confirmed to have West Nile virus died on Sat 14 Sep 2002
[see: West Nile virus, human - Canada (Ontario): fatal 20020917.5336].
******
[4]
Date: Mon 16 Sep 2002
From: <s.macbean@sasktel.net>
Source: Government of Manitoba, news release Bulletin 26, Fri 13 Sep
2002 [edited]

Manitoba: West Nile Virus Update
--------------------------------
Mosquitoes:
With 3 more positive mosquito pools identified in Winkler (1) and in
Winnipeg (2), the total comes to 10 positive pools so far this year.
Equines:
39 of the 65 horses reported yesterday are in the following RMs:
North Norfolk (1), South Norfolk (1), Langford (1), Miniota (4),
Turtle Mountain (2), Woodworth (8), Wallace (3), Sifton (2),
Winchester (2), Clanwilliam (1), Cornwallis (3), Rockwood (1), Tache
(1), Arthur (1), Morton (1), Riverside (1), Rosedale (2), Pipestone
(1), Springfield (1), North Cypress (1), and Louise(1). Confirmation
of the results on 14 of the horses reported yesterday is still
pending. Therefore, the total number of confirmed positive horses in
Manitoba is 87. Further information on the remaining horses will be
announced after their locations have been confirmed and the
municipalities have been notified.
Other species:
In Manitoba, the virus has also been previously found in birds of the
crow family, geese, ducks, sentinel chickens, and an owl. There have
been no human cases of West Nile virus diagnosed in this province.
The risk of illness for any individual remains low. New populations
of mosquitoes are less likely to be infected at this time of year.
--
<s.macbean@sasktel.net>
