[5]
Date: Wed 18 Sep 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Saskatchewan Health, West Nile virus update, Mon 16 Sep 2002 [edited]
<http://www.health.gov.sk.ca/rr_west_nile_update.html>

Saskatchewan: West Nile virus Update
------------------------------------
Birds:
The latest tests for West Nile Virus in Saskatchewan birds have
produced an additional 2 confirmed positive results in crows in
Rosetown (1) and Gull Lake (1), and 1 presumptive positive crow in
Semans. Birds that are presumed positive have been tested once at the
Health Canada laboratory and will undergo a second test to confirm
the positive result. This brings the total for confirmed West Nile
virus-positive birds to 25, plus 1 presumed positive bird. The birds
originated from 18 separate communities.
Equines:
The total for West Nile virus-positive equines remains at 6.
--
